Cape Town - Anchen Muller,13, from Brackenfell was found unharmed on Tuesday night. Police confirmed the young girl last seen at her family home on Friday, was found on Tuesday night at 22:35 in Bishop Lavis and is back with her family. Muller‘s family reported her missing on Monday, after she left home to attend a sleepover at a friend’s home in Table View, but never returned home. The Pink Ladies organisation and the local neighbourhood watch were also involved in the search for the teen, as the family turned to social media to help find her. Her mother, Hanlie Ferreira, confirmed her daughter had returned home unharmed and referred all other queries onto police. Cape Times